title: Minnesota wins 3rd WNBA title in 5 years
text: Minnesota wins 3rd WNBA title in 5 years Minnesota 69, Indiana 52 Hannah Foslien/Getty Images MINNEAPOLIS - Sylvia Fowles had 20 points and 11 rebounds to help the Minnesota Lynx capture the WNBA title Wednesday night, The Associated Press reported. More From KTVZ.COM The Lynx took their third championship in five years with a 69-52 win over the Indiana Fever. Seimone Augustus had 16 points, and Rebekkah Brunson had 14 rebounds for Minnesota. The Lynx got 21 turnovers from its defense, holding the Fever to a 35.7-percent shooting average. Maya Moore also scored just five points on 1-for-8 shooting for Minnesota. Leading for the Fever was Tamika Catchings, who had 18 points and 11 rebounds, the AP said. Distributed by LAKANA. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
